"{\"uid\": \"rnz.co.nz-international-pacific-news-523576-anatomy-of-a-wave-what-makes-the-olympic-surf-break-at-teahupo-o-unique-and-so-challenging\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"By Tom Shand* of Olympic views: the surf break at Teahupo'o with Tahiti Iti in the background.Photo:Getty Images / Ryan Pierse As the Olympics get going in earnest this week, not everyone's attention is focused on host city Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3, \"end\": 12, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Shand\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\"}, {\"begin\": 66, \"end\": 72, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.99995944319134, \"rank\": 4.0558453442867876e-05, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 226, \"end\": 231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999789170035, \"rank\": 2.1083001714830303e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic views\", \"from\": 17, \"to\": 30}, {\"ngram\": \"the surf\", \"from\": 32, \"to\": 40}, {\"ngram\": \"the background\", \"from\": 79, \"to\": 93}, {\"ngram\": \"Photo\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 99}, {\"ngram\": \"Getty Images\", \"from\": 100, \"to\": 112}, {\"ngram\": \"Ryan Pierse\", \"from\": 115, \"to\": 126}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 142}, {\"ngram\": \"earnest\", \"from\": 156, \"to\": 163}, {\"ngram\": \"not everyone's attention\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surf fans are heading to Tahiti, half a world away in French Polynesia.\", \"from\": 233, \"to\": 304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 258, \"end\": 264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.99995944319134, \"rank\": 4.0558453442867876e-05, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 294, \"end\": 303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9724341214261597, \"rank\": 0.028347296712942664, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Surf fans\", \"from\": 233, \"to\": 242}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why?\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 310, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, apart from the French coast resembling a lake at this time of year, on the south-west coast of Tahiti Iti is a wave unlike any other on the planet: Teahupo'o, which translates somewhat ominously as \\\"place of skulls\\\".\", \"from\": 311, \"to\": 533, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 332, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9970633181233245, \"rank\": 0.0023894197659813684, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lake\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 362}, {\"ngram\": \"this time\", \"from\": 366, \"to\": 375}, {\"ngram\": \"year\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 383}, {\"ngram\": \"the south-west coast\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 408}, {\"ngram\": \"Tahiti\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 418}, {\"ngram\": \"Iti\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 422}, {\"ngram\": \"a wave\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 432}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 463}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 474}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 521}, {\"ngram\": \"skulls\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 531}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wave is unique in the way it breaks.\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 575, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The wave\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 543}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 564}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The lower part of the wave appears to drop away below sea level, with the top half folding over dramatically to create an almost cartoonishly perfect form.\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 731, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The lower part\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 590}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 602}, {\"ngram\": \"sea level\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 639}, {\"ngram\": \"the top half\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 658}, {\"ngram\": \"an almost cartoonishly perfect form\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is both the weight of water in the plunging lip and the risk of injury or death for a surfer in the wrong position that make this one of the world's heaviest waves (in both senses of the word).\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 929, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the weight\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 754}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 763}, {\"ngram\": \"the plunging lip\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 783}, {\"ngram\": \"the risk\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 796}, {\"ngram\": \"injury\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 806}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 815}, {\"ngram\": \"a surfer\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 828}, {\"ngram\": \"the wrong position\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 850}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's heaviest waves\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 899}, {\"ngram\": \"both senses\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 915}, {\"ngram\": \"the word\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 927}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To understand why the wave breaks like this, we need to start with bathymetry: the shape of the seabed that influences waves as they approach the shore.\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 1083, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 957}, {\"ngram\": \"bathymetry\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1008}, {\"ngram\": \"the shape\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1019}, {\"ngram\": \"the seabed\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1033}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1055}, {\"ngram\": \"the shore\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1082}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At Teahupo'o, a combination of factors comes into play.\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1139, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a combination\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1111}, {\"ngram\": \"factors\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"play\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1138}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Waves arriving at Teahupo'o generally originate from intense \\\"roaring forties\\\" storm systems south of New Zealand.\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1255, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1243, \"end\": 1254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5649595053866897, \"rank\": 0.38934614215013214, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Waves\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1168}, {\"ngram\": \"intense \\\"roaring forties\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1218}, {\"ngram\": \"storm systems\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1233}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time the waves reach Tahiti they have become ordered swell, with wave heights of two to five metres and periods of 14 to 20 seconds between successive waves.\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.99995944319134, \"rank\": 4.0558453442867876e-05, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1267}, {\"ngram\": \"the waves\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1277}, {\"ngram\": \"wave heights\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1340}, {\"ngram\": \"two to five metres\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1362}, {\"ngram\": \"periods\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1374}, {\"ngram\": \"14 to 20 seconds\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1394}, {\"ngram\": \"successive waves\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1419}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These types of long-period waves normally start interacting with the seabed at depths of around 200 metres.\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1529, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These types\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1433}, {\"ngram\": \"long-period waves\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"the seabed\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1497}, {\"ngram\": \"depths\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1507}, {\"ngram\": \"around 200 metres\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1528}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On most coasts, this depth would occur up to several kilometres offshore.\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1603, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"most coasts\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1544}, {\"ngram\": \"this depth\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1556}, {\"ngram\": \"several kilometres\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1593}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But at Teahupo'o, it is much closer, just a couple of hundred metres.\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just a couple of hundred metres\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1672}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This rapid change in depth forces the wave to \\\"shoal\\\" very quickly - the wave speed slows, the distance between waves compresses and the wave height increases.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1834, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This rapid change\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1692}, {\"ngram\": \"depth forces\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1708}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1717}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave speed\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1758}, {\"ngram\": \"the distance\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1778}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave height increases\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1833}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The change is so abrupt that the wave is still very linear - it has not had time to develop the peaked crest and flat trough (the lowest part of the wave) typical of waves in shallow water.\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 2025, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The change\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1846}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 1916}, {\"ngram\": \"the peaked crest\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1944}, {\"ngram\": \"flat trough\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"the lowest part\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1977}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2007}, {\"ngram\": \"shallow water\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2024}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clockwise from top left: location of the Teahupo'o surf break, form of the reef and mountains behind, bathymetry of the surf break, and notable reef features (elevation data from SHOM, satellite imagery from Airbus).\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2027, \"end\": 2036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clockwise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.31411126677947e-44, \"text\": \"Clockwise\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clockwise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clockwise\"}, {\"begin\": 2206, \"end\": 2210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naval_Hydrographic_and_Oceanographic_Service\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"SHOM\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naval_Hydrographic_and_Oceanographic_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naval_Hydrographic_and_Oceanographic_Service\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"location\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2060}, {\"ngram\": \"the Teahupo'o surf break\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2088}, {\"ngram\": \"form\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2094}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2106}, {\"ngram\": \"mountains\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2120}, {\"ngram\": \"bathymetry\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2139}, {\"ngram\": \"the surf break\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2157}, {\"ngram\": \"notable reef features\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2184}, {\"ngram\": \"elevation data\", \"from\": 2186, \"to\": 2200}, {\"ngram\": \"satellite imagery\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2229}, {\"ngram\": \"Airbus\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Shand, CC BY-NC-SAPhoto:Tom Shand, CC BY-NC-SA Waves breaking on this type of steep slope would typically collapse, breaking from the middle of the wave and creating an unsurfable mess.\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2244, \"end\": 2253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Shand\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\"}, {\"begin\": 2255, \"end\": 2257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons_license\", \"score\": 0.9584295588292754, \"rank\": 0.028522571971996393, \"text\": \"CC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons_license\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons_license\"}, {\"begin\": 2272, \"end\": 2281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Shand\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Shand\"}, {\"begin\": 2283, \"end\": 2294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons_license\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CC BY-NC-SA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons_license\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons_license\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this type\", \"from\": 2313, \"to\": 2322}, {\"ngram\": \"steep slope\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2337}, {\"ngram\": \"the middle\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2388}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2400}, {\"ngram\": \"an unsurfable mess\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this does not happen.\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2460, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At around ten metres' depth, a flatter shelf in the reef allows the wave to stabilise and \\\"stand up\\\" with a steep front face, before finally breaking as the reef rises again.\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2636, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"around ten metres' depth\", \"from\": 2465, \"to\": 2489}, {\"ngram\": \"a flatter shelf\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2506}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef\", \"from\": 2510, \"to\": 2518}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2534}, {\"ngram\": \"a steep front face\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2586}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2623}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And break it does.\", \"from\": 2638, \"to\": 2656, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Owing to the linearity, there is far more water in the crest (the part above water) then most waves, and a deeper trough in front.\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2787, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the linearity\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2679}, {\"ngram\": \"far more water\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2704}, {\"ngram\": \"the crest\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2717}, {\"ngram\": \"the part\", \"from\": 2719, \"to\": 2727}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2739}, {\"ngram\": \"most waves\", \"from\": 2746, \"to\": 2756}, {\"ngram\": \"a deeper trough\", \"from\": 2762, \"to\": 2777}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 2781, \"to\": 2786}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This makes for the characteristic below-sea-level break at Teahupo'o, with the overturning lip being half the wave height, and a jet of compressed air forced out of the wave's barrel after breaking.\", \"from\": 2789, \"to\": 2987, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sea-level\", \"from\": 2829, \"to\": 2838}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2857}, {\"ngram\": \"the overturning lip\", \"from\": 2864, \"to\": 2883}, {\"ngram\": \"half the wave height\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2910}, {\"ngram\": \"a jet\", \"from\": 2916, \"to\": 2921}, {\"ngram\": \"compressed air\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 2939}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave's barrel\", \"from\": 2954, \"to\": 2971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The larger the wave, the closer to the steep offshore ramp it breaks, and the more extreme the plunging.\", \"from\": 2989, \"to\": 3093, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The larger the wave\", \"from\": 2989, \"to\": 3008}, {\"ngram\": \"the steep offshore ramp\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3047}, {\"ngram\": \"the more extreme the plunging\", \"from\": 3063, \"to\": 3092}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A typical breaking wave at Teahupo'o: the thick lip and deep trough make it so powerful.\", \"from\": 3095, \"to\": 3183, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A typical breaking wave\", \"from\": 3095, \"to\": 3118}, {\"ngram\": \"the thick lip\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3146}, {\"ngram\": \"deep trough\", \"from\": 3151, \"to\": 3162}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tim McKenna/Getty ImagesPhoto:Getty Images / Tim McKenna A range of other unique features contribute to the way the wave breaks at Teahupo'o - and what makes it so challenging as a surfing wave.\", \"from\": 3184, \"to\": 3380, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Getty ImagesPhoto\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3213}, {\"ngram\": \"Getty Images\", \"from\": 3214, \"to\": 3226}, {\"ngram\": \"Tim McKenna\", \"from\": 3229, \"to\": 3240}, {\"ngram\": \"other unique features\", \"from\": 3252, \"to\": 3273}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 3288, \"to\": 3295}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 3296, \"to\": 3304}, {\"ngram\": \"a surfing wave\", \"from\": 3363, \"to\": 3377}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A deep channel runs alongside the shallow reef shelf.\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3435, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A deep channel runs\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3401}, {\"ngram\": \"the shallow reef shelf\", \"from\": 3412, \"to\": 3434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wave does not break in this deeper area, allowing it to peel - to break in one direction (in this case towards the left looking towards the shore) - and enabling surfers to ride the wave before it finally closes out onto shallow reef.\", \"from\": 3436, \"to\": 3674, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The wave\", \"from\": 3436, \"to\": 3444}, {\"ngram\": \"this deeper area\", \"from\": 3463, \"to\": 3479}, {\"ngram\": \"one direction\", \"from\": 3515, \"to\": 3528}, {\"ngram\": \"this case\", \"from\": 3533, \"to\": 3542}, {\"ngram\": \"the shore\", \"from\": 3576, \"to\": 3585}, {\"ngram\": \"surfers\", \"from\": 3602, \"to\": 3609}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 3618, \"to\": 3626}, {\"ngram\": \"shallow reef\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A part of the shallow reef platform extends offshore, into the reef pass.\", \"from\": 3676, \"to\": 3749, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A part\", \"from\": 3676, \"to\": 3682}, {\"ngram\": \"the shallow reef platform\", \"from\": 3686, \"to\": 3711}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef pass\", \"from\": 3735, \"to\": 3748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This shallow area bends and focuses wave energy from the wider, deeper part of the wave back into the breaking wave.\", \"from\": 3750, \"to\": 3866, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This shallow area bends\", \"from\": 3750, \"to\": 3773}, {\"ngram\": \"wave energy\", \"from\": 3786, \"to\": 3797}, {\"ngram\": \"the wider, deeper part\", \"from\": 3803, \"to\": 3825}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 3829, \"to\": 3837}, {\"ngram\": \"the breaking wave\", \"from\": 3848, \"to\": 3865}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This happens particularly on more westerly orientated swells, increasing the intensity of breaking.\", \"from\": 3867, \"to\": 3966, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more westerly orientated swells\", \"from\": 3896, \"to\": 3927}, {\"ngram\": \"the intensity\", \"from\": 3940, \"to\": 3953}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 3965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as this, the Teahupo'o wave breaks in a direction nearly opposite to the prevailing trade winds, keeping the wave face smooth.\", \"from\": 3968, \"to\": 4102, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a direction\", \"from\": 4014, \"to\": 4025}, {\"ngram\": \"the prevailing trade winds\", \"from\": 4045, \"to\": 4071}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 4081, \"to\": 4089}, {\"ngram\": \"face\", \"from\": 4090, \"to\": 4094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A low tidal range also limits the times the reef is too deep or too shallow to surf.\", \"from\": 4104, \"to\": 4188, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A low tidal range\", \"from\": 4104, \"to\": 4121}, {\"ngram\": \"the times\", \"from\": 4134, \"to\": 4143}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef\", \"from\": 4144, \"to\": 4152}, {\"ngram\": \"surf\", \"from\": 4183, \"to\": 4187}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the wave is near the Passa Hava'e reef pass, which helps the wave's focusing and breaking.\", \"from\": 4189, \"to\": 4283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4214, \"end\": 4219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\", \"score\": 0.9999999954807208, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Passa\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passa,_Pyr\\u00e9n\\u00e9es-Orientales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 4193, \"to\": 4201}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 4250, \"to\": 4258}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 4274, \"to\": 4282}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But because it is not right in the pass, the wave is not affected by high tidal or wave-induced currents.\", \"from\": 4284, \"to\": 4389, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pass\", \"from\": 4315, \"to\": 4323}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 4325, \"to\": 4333}, {\"ngram\": \"high tidal or wave-induced currents\", \"from\": 4353, \"to\": 4388}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New-generation wave models that simulate individual waves, rather than just average energy density, provide insight into what creates a surf break such as Teahupo'o (see figure below).\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4575, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"New-generation wave models\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4417}, {\"ngram\": \"individual waves\", \"from\": 4432, \"to\": 4448}, {\"ngram\": \"just average energy density\", \"from\": 4462, \"to\": 4489}, {\"ngram\": \"insight\", \"from\": 4499, \"to\": 4506}, {\"ngram\": \"a surf break\", \"from\": 4525, \"to\": 4537}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 4546, \"to\": 4555}, {\"ngram\": \"figure\", \"from\": 4561, \"to\": 4567}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These models provide insight into what happens as waves shoal and refract (bend and focus) over the seabed as they approach break point.\", \"from\": 4576, \"to\": 4712, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These models\", \"from\": 4576, \"to\": 4588}, {\"ngram\": \"insight\", \"from\": 4597, \"to\": 4604}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 4626, \"to\": 4631}, {\"ngram\": \"the seabed\", \"from\": 4672, \"to\": 4682}, {\"ngram\": \"break point\", \"from\": 4700, \"to\": 4711}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They also significantly improve our understanding of what makes a particular surf break unique.\", \"from\": 4714, \"to\": 4809, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our understanding\", \"from\": 4746, \"to\": 4763}, {\"ngram\": \"a particular surf\", \"from\": 4778, \"to\": 4795}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This can help in assessing the potential impact of human or natural modifications to the environment.\", \"from\": 4810, \"to\": 4911, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the potential impact\", \"from\": 4837, \"to\": 4857}, {\"ngram\": \"human or natural modifications\", \"from\": 4861, \"to\": 4891}, {\"ngram\": \"the environment\", \"from\": 4895, \"to\": 4910}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An example of the Celeris wave model simulating typical surfing conditions at Teahupo'o.\", \"from\": 4913, \"to\": 5001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4931, \"end\": 4938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virtual_Pool\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Celeris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virtual_Pool\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Virtual_Pool\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An example\", \"from\": 4913, \"to\": 4923}, {\"ngram\": \"typical surfing conditions\", \"from\": 4961, \"to\": 4987}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The break point, peel angle and speed are able to be verified against satellite and drone imagery.\", \"from\": 5002, \"to\": 5100, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The break point\", \"from\": 5002, \"to\": 5017}, {\"ngram\": \"peel angle\", \"from\": 5019, \"to\": 5029}, {\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 5034, \"to\": 5039}, {\"ngram\": \"satellite and drone imagery\", \"from\": 5072, \"to\": 5099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Elevation data from SHOM, satellite imagery from Airbus.\", \"from\": 5101, \"to\": 5158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5122, \"end\": 5126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naval_Hydrographic_and_Oceanographic_Service\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"te